    "uid": "arxiv:2607.03510v1",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "management",
    "role": "object",
    "bullets": [
      "Conceptual framework paper with no empirical sample, aimed at enterprises moving agentic AI into operational workflows that plan, retrieve, call tools, and update systems.",
      "The paper uses no named model; it proposes CAGE-1, an evaluation framework spanning authority, policy enforcement, retrieval quality, memory integrity, tool safety, auditability, and human oversight, plus a Prebind Assurance concept.",
      "No empirical results are reported; the contribution is the framework and the idea of proving an agent action is controlled before it becomes binding or operationally consequential."
    ],
