    "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.6916779",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "management",
    "role": "object",
    "bullets": [
      "Conceptual essay on AI product development in the software industry, with no dataset or sample, arguing that few AI-native products embed in everyday user workflows beyond chatbots.",
      "No model is used or named; the paper proposes Product-Native AI, a two-stage Workflow Fit to Workflow Emergence pathway, and ten operational principles for teams.",
      "It argues the adoption gap is a product-experience problem rather than model capability, and prescribes placing intelligence at the right user moment through feedback."
    ],
